!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

attentive /əˈtɛntɪv/

1. ADJ If you are attentive , you are paying close attention to what is being said or done. 注意的 

例： He wishes the government would be more attentive to detail in their response. 他希望政府在回应时能更注意细节。 

2. attentively ADV 注意地 

例： He questioned Chrissie, and listened attentively to what she told him. 他询问了克丽茜，专注地听了她的讲述。 

3. ADJ Someone who is attentive is helpful and polite. 体贴的; 殷勤的 

例： At society parties he is attentive to his wife. 在社交聚会上，他对妻子体贴殷勤。

</div>

